reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Zu8U2TUWe-Dwy7BpanpgXYVw10qaY-REwGaYcvQxq-Y=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY5ZTY2MWI3OC0zMzU4LTRjMzItOWVkOC0zMzU5ZDExNzVhMzRfMzIwMHgyMTMyLmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/OjDLf_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux." alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ywBjqPAAkmk1tmAonMfKrzzNiCGgRCT9CcbEIoA-RNg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY5ZTY2MWI3OC0zMzU4LTRjMzItOWVkOC0zMzU5ZDExNzVhMzRfMzIwMHgyMTMyLmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/RLWAt3_aHANaYvybby0LlIMGGLhXAmnsNhWT2-5w5MM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGOWU2NjFiNzgtMzM1OC00YzMyLTllZDgtMzM1OWQxMTc1YTM0XzMyMDB4MjEzMi5qcGVn 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p><em>Photo by Kai Haskins</em></p><p>But there is a growing body of parties oriented around weed and psychedelics: The acid-laced, 36-hour techno party No Way Back, which takes place every Memorial Day weekend in Detroit. The growing microscene of ambient music events in Los Angeles and beyond, where shroom teas and chocolates are served over picnic blankets. The culture of California weed events, where due to legal restrictions around the sale of cannabis, no alcohol can be sold. These parties suggest that booze-free parties are not just possible—but preferable. </p><p>At Mushwomb, many headed straight to the booze-free bar to check out the array of trendy drink brands catering to the Cali Sober-curious. The adventurous went for spicy blood orange cocktails from <a href="https://bonbuz.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">bonbuz </a>that hit like crack in the face, thanks to green tea-derived caffeine and nootropics like L-tyrosine and 5-HTP. The grown and sexy gravitated towards botanical brews from <a href="https://optimistdrinks.com/products/optimist-spirit-smokey" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Optimist,</a> particularly a smoky potion of sage, ginger, cloves, and habanero. Stoners opted for cans of THC-infused sparkling water from <a href="https://calexo.co/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Calexo</a>, delivered to the club earlier that day by two moustached gays in tiny shorts and roller skates. </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F03ab6180-0a75-4af8-a2b0-cc0b3550744a_2000x1600.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/9DI7A_bh12tomYpGTMLsAsvCM_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/HI6O-VXsC6JH7z8o0Dch9HnP_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/yRKcNSyX14m1EXvt_hJqvAZX8xShaggj9IYpx0_zVO4=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMDNhYjYxODAtMGE3NS00YWY4LWEyYjAtY2MwYjM1NTA3NDRhXzIwMDB4MTYwMC5wbmc= 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/eC27inEQUOLDTjwDL-" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/dVrTKjaP__NBHE_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/7sIOPTDJavNERBSYRjVwgbzcJyPPDYjKR-wgnPhy2Dk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkYwM2FiNjE4MC0wYTc1LTRhZjgtYTJiMC1jYzBiMzU1MDc0NGFfMjAwMHgxNjAwLnBuZw== 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/eC27inEQUOLDTjwDL- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p><em>The wild world of weed sodas, CBG joints, and zero-proof cocktails…</em> </p><p>Learning to socialize on other substances is a mode of engagement that could be learned through new communal experiences, especially since it is not yet supported by the media or culturally-accepted rites of passage (like college binge drinking). Shroom raves could open up new modes of social engagement: introspective, meditative, empathetic, tranquil, attuned to the energetic instead of verbal. What if we could normalize hugging on the dancefloor, instead of slurring speech into each others’ ears? </p><p>Come nightfall, the Mushwomb dancefloor was heaving, and DJ Ty’s blend of jubilant house and garage was like a joyride for the soul—a feeling of peaking suspended. By now, the vibe shift was apparent: without the drowsy depressant of alcohol, bodies bounced with the buoyancy of clean energy and lips curled into grins—even the air smelled fresher somehow. In between the contagious euphoria—the locomotive propulsion of truly getting your groove on—strangers exchanged looks: <em>do you feel it, too?</em> Then came SPRKLBB’s propulsive tech-house as the dancefloor coalesced into an orgiastic sea of bodies, momentum building into a climatic roar. </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc9187b4f-533b-4e22-91cc-d5858722a145_3200x2130.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><sou